description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen in the Diabetes and Endocrinology department for a Clinical Lead Nurse. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Diabetes and Endocrinology department at the Royal Berkshire Hospital is a transformational clinic setting that cares for both Outpatients and Inpatients. The department currently provides the following services:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;An inpatient service between 09:00 – 17:00 seven days per week&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Telephone clinics for outpatients&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Follow-up clinics for outpatients&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;DSN Clinics &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Young Adult Clinic (YAC)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Nurse virtual follow-up for YAC&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Complex clinics &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Continuous Glucose Monitoring (CGM) clinic &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;CGM virtual follow-up clinic.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Freestyle Libre (FSL) service&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Dexcom CGM clinics&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Insulin Pump clinics&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Referrals from GP’s&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Diabetes clinics (Cons / SpR led) Nurse cover &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Endocrinology clinics and day cases&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We are looking for a high skilled, motivated, enthusiastic and a compassionate leader to join the team. The post holder will provide enhanced management skills to lead the team. They will provide support for senior nursing staff in relation to staff development, complaints and lead and guide both nursing and medical staff in the appropriate and timely care of patients. The highly qualified post holder will be able to act as a resource providing advice, support and guidance to all members of the healthcare team both within the directorate and Trust wide. The post holder will be an agent for change, monitoring and evaluating practices. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
